The Turkish army shelled a police station for YPG in Ain Diwar in the north eastern countryside of Al-Hasakeh, no casualties were reported.

assoc_actor_1: Operation Olive Branch; Opposition Rebels (Syria); Islamist Militia (Syria)
notes: Clashes took place between Turkish forces and rebel and Islamist factions of the Turkish "Operation Olive Branch" against YPG and Self-Defense Forces in Qurna village in northern Aleppo. Olive Branch FSA forces took control of the village. No fatalities reported.

assoc_actor_1: Operation Olive Branch; Opposition Rebels (Syria); Islamist Militia (Syria)
notes: Clashes and Turkish shelling took place between Turkish forces and rebel and Islamist factions of the Turkish "Operation Olive Branch" against YPG and Self-Defense Forces in Afrin, concentrated in the Jandaris sub-district of northern Aleppo. Turkish warplanes also raided the area, targeting YPG positions, areas in the Jandairis town in Afrin in Aleppo, killing a young boy and injuring another civilian. Clashes in Jabal Barsaya, Qastal Jandu, Bulbul, Raju, Jandaris, and Hamam killed at least 13 Olive Branch and Turkish forces and 6 YPG and Self-Defense Force fighters. The bodies of 2 Turkish soldiers were taken by YPG forces from the battlefield. 19 fatalities split between 6 locations, with Jabal Barsaya allocated 4 and Qastal Jandu, Bulbul, Raju, Jandaris, and Hamam each allocated 3. Total fatalities coded as 4.

Turkish warplanes also targeted Raju area, killing 1 civilian. Total fatalities coded as 4.

notes: Clashes, accompanied by Turkish airstrikes, took place between Turkish forces and rebel and Islamist factions of the Turkish "Operation Olive Branch" against YPG and Self-Defense Forces in Sheikh El-Hadid village in northern Aleppo. No fatalities reported.
Turkish forces shelled areas of the Afrin countryside, including the Shirawa area, as Turkish warplanes struck YPG positions in the area. No fatalities reported.
Turkish warplanes carried out raids on Helwaniya, Kindi, and Mazn towns as well as other YPG targets in the Sharan sub-district. No fatalities reported.

assoc_actor_1: Operation Olive Branch; Opposition Rebels (Syria); Islamist Militia (Syria)
notes: Clashes took place between Turkish forces and rebel and Islamist factions of the Turkish "Operation Olive Branch" against YPG fighters in the Shenkal area of northern Aleppo. No fatalities reported.
Turkish fighter jets bombed areas in the vicinity of the Maydanki Dam in the Afrin area of northern Aleppo, targeting YPG positions. No fatalities reported.

assoc_actor_1: Operation Olive Branch; JSH: Free Syrian Army
notes: Turkish and allied FSA Olive Branch forces shelled YPG position in the western vicinity of Jabal Barsaya. YPG positions in the area were destroyed by Turkish Firtina Howitzers and Turkish forces shelled the area with a Rokestan T-122. Olive Branch fighters reportedly captured YPG trenches and interconnected concrete tunnels in the area. No fatalities reported.
Clashes took place between Turkish and YPG forces in the village of Khalil in Mabata district of Afrin. No fatalities reported.
Turkish forces shelled YPG positions in Shuyukh with artillery. No fatalities reported.
Turkish warplanes carried out raids against the YPG in Bashmra town in northern Aleppo. No fatalities reported.
Turkish warplanes carried out raids against the YPG in Basufan town in the Afrin district of northern Aleppo. No fatalities reported.
Turkish warplanes reportedly hit YPG positions near Tell Abiad in Ar-Raqqa province, including a hill to the town's south. No fatalities reported.
Turkish warplanes carried out strikes against the YPG in A'rima town in northern Aleppo. No fatalities reported.
YPG fighters targeted Turkish army positions in Bazara village, between Darat Azza and Basufan in northern Aleppo. No fatalities reported.
Turkish army forces shelled YPG positions in Jarablus city with artillery. No fatalities reported.

assoc_actor_1: JSH: Free Syrian Army; JWS: Syrian National Army; Opposition Rebels (Syria); Islamist Militia (Syria)
notes: Operation Olive Branch FSA forces announced the capture of Omar Ushaghi village in northern Afrin from YPG forces. National Syrian Army forces were also present. No fatalities reported.
Turkish military forces shelled a YPG outpost north of the town of Amuda. No information about damage or casualties reported.

YPG sources said that Turkish warplanes carried out raids on villages in the Afrin area amid heavy clashes. Part of the clashes came from Turkish forces opening a new front on Afrin originating from the Az'az area.
Turkish warplanes struck YPG positions in the Karatshouk Mountains in rural al-Malikeyyeh with no information about damage or casualties reported.
Turkish warplanes struck YPG positions in the town of Jandairis, killing 1 civilian.
Turkish military forces shelled Kashto farm, near Ras Al Ain, which may have resulted in YPG casualties. Accounting for fatalities coded in Ras Al Ain town, no fatalities coded to this event.
Turkish warplanes carried out raids against YPG targets in the Raju area and nearby villages, killing 2 civilians and injuring as many as 14 more.
Turkish military forces and their Euphrates Shield allies tried to enter the YPG-held town of Jandaris with neither injuries nor fatalities reported.
Turkish military forces shelled YPG positions in the Baflune mountains with neither injuries nor fatalities reported.
Turkish T-122 MLRS units launched missiles at YPG positions in the town of Afrin. No information about damage or casualties reported.

FSA 9th Brigade Special Forces units took part in the Afrin offensive. YPG forces claimed to have destroyed a Turkish tank as part of a clash somewhere in Afrin province. Neither injuries nor fatalities reported.
The Turkish warplanes conducted several air strikes on YPG positions in Marata village in Afrin district in the northern countryside of Aleppo, no casualties were reported.

Turkish troops conducted several artillery strikes on YPG positions in several areas and townships of Afrin district which killed as many as 6 civilians and injured several others. The attack also killed 3 YPG fighters. Total fatalities coded as 9.
The Turkish warplanes conducted several air strikes on YPG positions in Afrin city in the northern countryside of Aleppo, no casualties were reported.
The Turkish army shelled YPG positions in the Afrin area in the northern countryside of Aleppo, no casualties were reported.
The Turkish army shelled the positions of YPG militia in Bulbul town in Afrin District in the northern countryside of Aleppo, no casualties were reported.
Turkish military forces shelled the YPG-controlled village of Aud al-Dadad in rural Menbij with neither injuries nor fatalities reported.
Turkish military forces shelled YPG positions in Jarablus with neither injuries nor fatalities reported.
Turkish military forces shelled the YPG-positions in areas around Afrin with no casualties reported.
Turkish forces shelled the Afrin area, including Villat al-Qadi village, likely in the Raju area of northern Syria. 1 YPG fighter and 5 civilians were killed in shelling on the area.

Turkish forces fired artillery shells on YPG targets in the town of Basufan in northern Aleppo. Shelling on Qatma, Kafr Janna, Upper Maskeh, Raju, Iskan, Basufan, Deir Ballut, Jalama, Jandairis, and other areas caused material damage. No fatalities reported.

Turkish forces fired artillery shells on YPG targets in the town of Deir Ballut in northern Aleppo. Shelling on Qatma, Kafr Janna, Upper Maskeh, Raju, Iskan, Basufan, Deir Ballut, Jalama, Jandairis, and other areas caused material damage. No fatalities reported.

Turkish forces fired artillery shells on YPG targets in Jandaris city in northern Aleppo and areas in its vicinity. Shelling on Qatma, Kafr Janna, Upper Maskeh, Raju, Iskan, Basufan, Deir Ballut, Jalama, Jandairis, and other areas caused material damage. No fatalities reported.

Turkish forces fired artillery shells on YPG targets in the village of Jisr Hashraka in the Raju sub-district of northern Aleppo as well as other places in the area. Shelling on Qatma, Kafr Janna, Upper Maskeh, Raju, , Deir Ballut, Jalama, Jandairis, and other areas caused material damage. No fatalities reported.

Sporadic clashes took place between Turkish forces and YPG fighters on the Turkish-Syrian border, likely in the Afrin district of Aleppo, as the 2 sides also exchanged heavy machine gun fire. No fatalities reported.
Turkish military forces shelled YPG positions in the Afrin countryside, injuring two civilians, including a child. It was reported that 1 YPG fighter was killed by the shelling.
Turkish military forces shelled YPG positions in the village of Iskan with no information about fatalities reported.
A Turkish UAV struck a YPG position in Qastal Jandu in northern Aleppo. No fatalities reported.
At least one YPG fighter was killed by Turkish military shelling of the town of Afrin.
3 YPG fighters from the Syrian Democratic Forces were killed by Turkish forces in the countryside of Afrin under unknown circumstances.
Turkish forces shelled YPG positions in Basufan village with artillery. No fatalities reported.
Turkish forces shelled YPG positions in Ba'ay village with artillery. No fatalities reported.

The Turkish army clashed with the YPG and YPJ militias in the northern part of Afrin district near the Turkish border amid shelling by the Turkish army on the villages north of Afrin district, the clashes led to injure 1 militant of the Turkish army, no fatalities were reported.
Turkish forces shelled YPG positions in Dikmetash village, in the vicinity of Meidan Ekbis in northern Aleppo, with artillery. No fatalities reported.
Turkish military forces shelled YPG positions in the village of Basufan in Afrin district. No information about casualties.
Turkish artillery targeted YPG Positions in Jinderes in Aleppo governorate. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.
Turkish artillery in Jarablus area hit YPG positions near Shekler/Sheykh Fawqani in Aleppo governorate. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.
Gunshots were heard in the Afrin area, believed to be caused by exchange of targeting between YPG fighters in Afrin and Turkish forces positioned in the area. One YPG fighter was reported killed.
Turkish military forces attacked YPG positions in the village of Iskan on the Turkish border. No information about casualties reported.
YPG downed a Turkish drone in Afrin area of Aleppo over Mount Gir in Beke village. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.
YPG fighters clashed with Turkish military forces as the former tried to cross into Turkey. No information about casualties provided.

Four suspected YPG members were detained by Turkish border guards while attempting to illegally cross into Turkey from northern Syria. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported. Suspected location Al-Hasakeh.
YPG arrested several of its fighters on charges of smuggling refugees from Al-Sadd camp in Shadadi in the countryside of Al-Hasakeh. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.
Turkish military forces shelled Kurdish positions, likley YPG, in Afrin using heavy artillery. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.
YPG fought the Turkish military in Shahbah of eastern Afrin. No losses reported.
Turkish military forces fought YPG in Sheikh Issa. No deaths reported.

actor2: Mutiny of YPG: Peoples Protection Units
notes: Clashes broke in Kherbet She'eer near Tell Temer in Alhassakeh between YPG and a defector from YPG. The defector along with 3 YPG fighters were killed in the clashes.
Turkish warplanes targeted YPG positions in Derek (Al-Malikiyah) of Al-Hasakeh governorate. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.
Turkish Army shelled YPG positions in Minag village of Aleppo governorate. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.
Turkish Army shelled YPG positions in Maranaz village of Aleppo governorate. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.
YPG downed a Turkish reconnaissance plane flying over Afrin of Aleppo, and the plane fell in Bara village of Daret Aze town of Aleppo. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.
Turkish armed forces shelled YPG positions in Afrin area of Aleppo governorate. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.
Turkish artillery targeted a YPG police station in Amouda in Alhassakeh. Neither injuries nor fatalities reported.

Turkish artillery targeted YPG positions in the town of Khaarzeh in Amouda's countryside in Alhassakeh. Neither injuries nor fatalities reported.
Turkish artillery targeted YPG positions in the town of Hamdouneh in Amouda's countryside in Alhassakeh. Neither injuries nor fatalities reported.
Clashes between Turkish and YPG forces broke near Ra'as Alain in the northern countryside of Alhassakeh. Neither injuries nor fatalities reported.
Turkish Army shelled YPG forces near Raas Alain in Alhassakeh. Neither injuries nor fatalities reported.
Clashes between the Turkish army and YPG forces near Jattal village in Alderbasyeh in Alhassakeh. Neither injuries nor fatalities reported.
YPG forces targeted Turkish soldiers at "Shih" near Afrin, and exchanged shelling. There no reported fatalities.
YPG forces clashed with Turkish soldiers at Raju in Aleppo province. There were no reported fatalities.
YPG destroyed, possibly by shelling or missile strikes, nine tanks and five military points of the Turkish Army killing 22 soldiers in northern Syria. Suspected location Al-Hasakah.
Turkish Army targeted with tanks and howitzers YPG positions in Tel Halaf west of Ras Al-Ain in Al-Hasakah governorate. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.
Turkish Army attacked Afrin canton bombarding Mullah Khalil and Ceqela Jorin in Shia district, and the YPG responded to the attack. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.
Turkish Army targeted with tanks and howitzers YPG positions in Aluk Al-Gharbi east of Tal Abyad in Ar-Raqqa governorate. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.

Turkish Army bombarded YPG units in Tal Abyad in Ar-Raqqa governorate with howitzers. YPG fighters returned fire, hitting a Turkish Army tank with an ATGM near Tal Abyad. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.

An exchange of fire between the Turkish Army and YPG forces took place near Jattal village near Aldirbasyeh and in Ala'rada village in Raas Alain countryside. Neither injuries nor fatalities reported.
Clashes took place between YPG and YPJ and Turkish Army as YPG and YPJ targeted a Turkish tank that tried to cross to Syria in Al-Hasakahh governorate. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.
3 Turkish soldiers were killed and 5 others were wounded during clashes with YPG forces in Dirbasiyah borders in Al-Hasak governorate. A number of YPG members were also killed during the clashes.
The Turkish army targeted YPG forces in Alderbasyeh, leading to fatalities. Unknown number of fatalities coded as 10.
Turkish warplanes raided YPG headquarters in Jabal Qarjokh near Almalkyeh (deirek), leading to deaths and injuries. Unknown number of fatalities coded as 10.
Turkish warplanes killed 20 YPG fighters and injured 18, among which three are in a critical condition in Al-Hasakah governorate.
Turkish airstrikes killed 18 of YPG affiliates in Derek, north-eastern Syria.
YPG fighters clashed with Turkish military forces in the Jabal Gher area of Afrin near the Turkish border.
Turkish howitzers pounded targets of Peoples Protection Units to the south to Azaz as an exchange of shelling took place in the same area. No reported casualties.
People protections units shelled positions of Turkish soldiers in Al Bab with mortar fire. 4 servicemen were reported injuried.
Turkish jets bombarded the positions of the Peoples Protection Units in Um Jlud village. No reported casualties.
Turkish Army clashed with Peoples Protection Units near Bulbul town. No reported casualties.
Turkish forces artillery shelled Peoples Protection Units targets in Maraanaz village. No information about fatalities.
Turkish forces artillery shelled Peoples Protection Units targets in A'rima town. No information about fatalities.
Turkish forces artillery shelled Peoples Protection Units targets in Al Kawukli village. No information about fatalities.
Clashes took place between YPG and Turkish forces around Ghar mount near Afrin after an attack by the Turkish forces on the area, no reports of casualties.
Turkish forces shelled Peoples Protection Units targets in Maraanaz village. No information about fatalities.
Turkish military forces targeted, likely with shelling, positions of YPG in Mazra village near Al-Malkiyeh city of Al-Hasakeh governorate. Neither fatalities nor injuries were reported.
Turkish forces targeted, likely with shelling, positions of YPG in Upper Shyoukh village in the countryside of Ain Al-Arab city. No information about casualties.
Turkish forces targeted, likely with shelling, positions of YPG in Jaregli area in the countryside of Ayn Al-Arab in Aleppo governorate. No information about casualties.
Turkish Gendarmerie killed a number of Kurdish YPG fighters a they were trying to smuggle weapons from Tal Kharnoub village into the Turkish territories. Unknown fatalities coded as 10.
The Turkish army shelled the YPG's positions north of A'rima village in the eastern countryside of Aleppo. No casualties were reported.
